[32;8m  === Network ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[33;8m  ===================================================================================================
 
  Installed is the MIAMIDX TCP/IP as default stack and WiFiPi as the default network device.
   A Wlan Prism2 device can also be used as well the good old PlipBox.
   Use TopMenu>>Network>>Network Device Selector to select the network device driver.
   Here the network device can be selected and it will become the default one.
   Make sure to setup your SSID and WPA. TopMenu>>Network>>Wlan Prefs
   TCP-IP Stack:
   You can choose between MiamiDX and Roadshow for default TCP-IP Stack.
   Installed is the demo Roadshow library. You have to provide your own for full functionality.
   A requester will ask for your 'bsdsocket.library'. No need to use the RoadShow installer!  
   Use the Network Preferences tools located in Sys:Prefs/Network to configure the various options.
   When using MiamiDX, a Stats panel can be requested by pressing Ctrl-LAlt+j.
  
  FTP
   A FTP client is available for use. CaffeineOS button>>Network>>Ftp>>FtpConnect
   Alternative is RNOXfer.
 
  SAMBA
   The SMB file system wrapper from Olaf Barthel and SMB2 are installed.
  To configure Samba:
  use the configuration tool by clicking on the CaffeineOS button>>Network>>Samba>>Config Smbfs/Smb2.
 
