[32;8m  === WHDLoad ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[33;8m  ===================================================================================================
 
  To achieve better compatibility with some games, the JIT is manipulated to slowdown at starting
  Whdload demos and games (Turtle Mode).
  For that we use the WHDLoadWrapper which is a helper tool for WHDLoad.
  Some games run better with custom settings. Depending on the RPI used, a database containing
  predefined settings is available.
  
  The Database file contains the options that are needed and then applies those options 
  before WHDLoad is executed.
  You find the databases inside the S:WHDLoad-Wrapper folder. 
  For more information, see the included Readme.  
      
  Press F10 to quit a game loaded by WHDLOAD. If F10 does not work, try PrtSc (*) or DEL
  The WHDLoad Splash window informs about the defined quit key

