[32;8m  *I have a DS3231 RTC in my Expansion Breakout. How do I set the date and time?
        -> With CaffeineOS the I2C real time clock is detected and the following is true:
           If you have internet, the clock will update the date/time and save it automatically.
           To update the time manually
           Open a Cli window and type:
           DATE DD-MMM-YYYY HH:MM:SS Press ENTER
           I2Clock CHIP=DS3231 SAVE Press ENTER
